Reply. It is granted, many die of the fore-mentioned diſeaſes that were never Dipt, and (I hope) have continued ſuch trees to the death, as have have had no cauſe to be aſhamed of their fruit. But I am aſhamed of your ſcurrility, and abuſe of Mr. Baxter, who ſaith, Dipping in cold water, in cold weather, is one (not the one
